caption: The experience at Tabaré was excellent. From the point of making the reservation over the phone to paying the bill, everything was on point! Menu is short to the point, which I like because it's not overwhelming and the restaurant focuses more on giving quality than providing a 10 page menu that may not be good in everything. Food was delicious. My wife had the Churrasco with potatoes, salad, and chimichurri sauce and I had the chivito that brings french fries. Both dishes were phenomenal! We also had the empanadas for appetizer and they were legit. They have a prefix brunch menu on the weekends at a reasonable price and have good cocktails at unbeatable price during happy hours. Besides the food, the place has a great bohemian vintage vibe with a rustic look that makes it feel cozy due to its size. Good place to go with friends and family and feel like home. Last but not least, the service was great. We were lucky enough to be attended by the owner Ramiro who is very kind and took the time to explain the menu and even took a picture with us at end. He also mentioned that he has another location in Bushwick which we are planning to visit in the near future. Five stars to this place no doubt and thanks Ramiro for the good hospitality.

The only reason I gave this place a 4/5 was because it was cash/amex only and they didn't tell us till the very end and I didn't see it posted anywhere except the desert menu.The food was very good. Tasted fresh the service was quick and dinner for two was way less then expected. 👍 Will definitely come back but bring cash.

I went at 4:30 when the kitchen wasn't ready for Dinner and the staff was scrambling. It's hard to rate some places post Covid in NYC especially the smaller ones with less staff or are owner operated because they Naturally have a disadvantage. The beef empanadas were to die for. The best empanadas I’ve had in New York so far. I also got the homemade pappardelle which was delicious! My friend got the chicken Milanese and he really enjoyed it. Looking forward to coming back to try the other dishes on the menu! The service was great as well! It was a papperdelle with meat ragu and tasted perfect. My friend ordered the sea bass, and the other ordered the gnocchi. Both said their dishes were wonderful. It was frustrating when it came to pay, they don't even have an ATM on site, so I gave her a look and I was like can you accept a regular card this one time? She asked the owner who agreed but only to take one card not all 3 which was fine. The other option would be walking down the block to get money from a deli.  Anyways, if you are like me and don't appreciate restaurants that are cash only, this is not the place for you.

The manager managed to seat us while waiting for a large party to show up afterwards and the service was quick, but not rushed which was much appreciated. Prices for food and wine were high to me, but payed for themselves in quality.

Went here on a very cold Friday night in a date. I absolutely love that we only made the reservation 20 mins ahead of time and they were able to take us. The place, from what I could see (will mention this more), is small but very nice, well decorated, great music, not too loud; would recommend for a date spot. The only thing I didn't like too much was that it was so dark that I could barely see the menu; it was mostly lit by candlight. The food was very good. I had the beef and chicken empanadas and the milanesa de pollo; both were very delicious. My only complaints are that they only take cash or American express (which we didn't know until it was time to pay), their prices are kinda high, and the wait staff seemed annoyed by humans in general.

I'm laughing now but I'm terrified of rats! We ran inside to let the waiter now and they said they were sorry for and so on and the other waiter went on to say how it was out of their control, and seemed unbothered by my discomfort. Neither of them offered to take anything off our bill for the discomfort. After speaking so highly of this place to my friend I felt disappointed and disgusted by them. I live a block away and this will probably by the last place I recommend to anyone now.

Giving this two stars only for the atmosphere and architecture. The place is absolutely beautiful, but thats all it has going for it.  The waiters are really nice too. The drinks, for their price are delicious but WEAK. I'm a total light-weight, I can have one glass of rum and I'll be tipsy. I ordered one of their drinks and I didn't even feel a tinge of alcohol. The fact that they only take cash and American Express. Thats ridiculous, no exceptions. The food, you think you're going to get something fantastic, because boy oh boy do the reviews seem to say you will but my sandwich was soggy as hell. There was just so much going on in the sandwich. There was no egg or bacon, as claimed in the menu, but soggy ham and less than toasted bread. I'm utterly disappointed. I had high hopes for this place. My last issue is the PRICE. Google gives this place $ which signifies its cheap. That makes no freaking sense. This place is not cheap at all. Their menu has little options and everything is expensive. To me, $ means prices similar to Vanessa's Dumpling's which is good cheap food. Or even SEA which never breaks the bank even when I pay for a drink and for a meal. The price tag is ridiculously misleading. The food is not superb in any special way or form. Maybe the lighting and architecture of the places convinces customers its actually better than it is. This is an exaggerated rating. I did love my waitress, Mariana though.

I love the atmosphere and the cocktails (we tried the Zabala and El Gaucho) are great! It was not very busy for brunch. We had the revuelto Gramajo and the chivito which were both good. My only complaint is that there was too much salt and pepper on the chivito. The fries and aioli it came with were perfect.  We also had the Martin Fierro for dessert, and I have to say that I was taken aback by the fact that it's just cheese, quince paste, and pieces of walnut. No bread or pastry to bring them together. That would be ok for an appetizer (in fact, I serve this as finger food when I host get togethers) but for dessert it's odd. I have never been served that as a dessert in Uruguay, by the way.  The bathroom was clean, the back garden was cute, and the wait staff was very nice. I wish the dinner menu had more entrees on it, but otherwise it is a good place to eat.
Great place for a date. Pricey but cozy and delicious and worth it.

Had a dinner there the other day with my husband. The atmosphere was romantic, the place was not too crowded and the customer service was good. Although the food was delicious, even though the pork chops are over spiced for my taste, the food gave us both upset stomach for two days. We have never had this happen to us after eating in a restaurant so I am just a little surprised that nobody had mentioned it before in their reviews. Also it wasn't cheap to eat out there to be so sick, plus they don't take anything besides Amex or cash. I wouldn't recommend this place.
